# Collection Structure

This is an Ansible collection (`lb2961.ai_driven_aap`) with roles for deploying an AIOps workshop stack.

## Role Layout

Each role follows standard Ansible structure:
```
roles/<role_name>/
  defaults/main.yml   # Default variables (overridden by agnosticv common.yaml)
  tasks/main.yml      # Task logic
  templates/           # Jinja2 templates (if needed)
  meta/main.yml        # Role metadata
```

## Key Roles

| Role | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `splunk` | Splunk Enterprise in Podman with Cisco + EDA apps |
| `kafka` | Apache Kafka in Podman (KRaft mode) |
| `filebeat` | Filebeat shipping Apache logs to Kafka |
| `winlogbeat` | Windows event logs to Kafka |
| `mattermost` | Mattermost chat with webhooks |
| `rhelai_model_serve` | InstructLab / RHEL AI model serving |
| `mcp_server` | AAP MCP server container |
| `lightspeed_mcp_server` | Red Hat Lightspeed MCP container |
| `code_server_ai_client` | Claude Code or Continue.dev setup |
| `continue_dev_config` | Continue.dev config with MCP servers |
| `eda_project_sync_wait` | EDA project sync via AAP API |
| `controller_firewall` | Opens firewall for EDA webhooks |
| `gitea_create` | Gitea repo + PAT creation |

## Custom Module

`plugins/modules/yaml_edit.py` — edits YAML files by path while preserving structure. Requires `ruamel.yaml`. Used as `lb2961.ai_driven_aap.yaml_edit`.

## Conventions

- Containers run in **Podman** (not Docker)
- Roles use `become: true` for privileged operations
- Default passwords derive from `common_password` (set in agnosticv)
- S3-hosted artifacts are downloaded at deploy time (not baked in)
- Roles should be idempotent — safe to re-run
